2026-02-20 11:03:53 - INFO - 716 -{"tools": [], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "You are an expert Travel Planner assistant specializing in creating detailed holiday itineraries.\n\nYour role is to:\n1. Create a comprehensive day-by-day travel plan based on the user's destination country and number of days\n2. Suggest popular tourist attractions and activities for each day\n3. Recommend suitable hotels with different budget categories (budget, mid-range, luxury)\n4. Calculate approximate budget breakdown including:\n   - Accommodation costs per night\n   - Daily food expenses\n   - Transportation costs\n   - Attraction entry fees\n   - Total estimated trip cost\n\nInput from user: Country/City and Number of Days\n\nOutput format:\n- Day-by-day itinerary with morning, afternoon, and evening activities\n- Hotel suggestions with approximate prices\n- Budget calculator with itemized costs\n- Travel tips and recommendations\n\nBe specific, practical, and provide realistic time estimates for each activity.", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "I want to two day trip to goa with the budget of 50000. Can you help me plan it?"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-53294bd5-1347-4b37-9453-2a2a558e0b56", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "stop", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": "## 2\u2011Day Goa Getaway \u2013 INR\u202f50,000 (\u2248\u202f\u20b925,000 per day)\n\nBelow is a **ready\u2011to\u2011use** plan that covers:\n\n* **Day\u2011by\u2011day itinerary** (morning\u202f/\u202fafternoon\u202f/\u202fevening) with realistic travel times.  \n* **Hotel recommendations** for three budget tiers (budget, mid\u2011range, luxury) with per\u2011night rates.  \n* **Itemised budget calculator** (accommodation, food, transport, entry fees, misc).  \n* **Practical travel tips** (how to move around, what to pack, safety, best time to visit).\n\n---\n\n## 1\ufe0f\u20e3 DAY\u2011BY\u2011DAY ITINERARY  \n\n> **Assumptions** \u2013 You\u2019ll arrive in Goa by flight or train the night before Day\u202f1 (or early on Day\u202f1). The plan starts from **Panaji (the capital)**, which is a convenient base for both North and South Goa. All times are approximate and can be shifted by a few minutes depending on traffic and personal pace.\n\n| Day | Time | Activity | Details & Travel Time |\n|-----|------|----------|-----------------------|\n| **Day\u202f1 \u2013 North Goa Highlights** | **08:00\u202f\u2013\u202f09:00** | **Breakfast** at the hotel or a local caf\u00e9 (e.g., *Cafe Bodega*). | Typical Indian breakfast: idli\u2011vada, poha, fresh juice \u2013 \u20b9150\u2011\u20b9250. |\n| | **09:00\u202f\u2013\u202f10:30** | **Fort Aguada & Lighthouse** | 5\u202fkm from Panaji (\u2248\u202f15\u202fmin by scooter). Entry free; small fee for lighthouse (\u20b920). |\n| | **10:30\u202f\u2013\u202f12:00** | **Sinquerim Beach** \u2013 quick dip or sunrise walk. | 2\u202fkm from Fort Aguada (\u2248\u202f5\u202fmin). |\n| | **12:00\u202f\u2013\u202f13:30** | **Lunch** at *Martin\u2019s Corner* (Baga) \u2013 Goan seafood thali. | \u20b9350\u2011\u20b9500. |\n| | **13:30\u202f\u2013\u202f15:30** | **Calangute & Baga Beaches** \u2013 water\u2011sports (optional jet\u2011ski, parasailing). | Activity cost: \u20b9800\u2011\u20b91,200 per person (choose one). |\n| | **15:30\u202f\u2013\u202f16:30** | **Anjuna Flea Market** (Wednesday\u2011Saturday) \u2013 shop for souvenirs, jewellery, handicrafts. | No entry fee; budget \u20b9500\u2011\u20b91,000 for shopping. |\n| | **16:30\u202f\u2013\u202f18:00** | **Chapora Fort** \u2013 sunset view over Vagator Beach. | 6\u202fkm from Anjuna (\u2248\u202f15\u202fmin). Entry free. |\n| | **18:00\u202f\u2013\u202f20:00** | **Dinner** at *Thalassa* (Vagator) \u2013 Greek\u2011Goan fusion, great sunset vibe. | \u20b9600\u2011\u20b9900 per person. |\n| | **20:00\u202f\u2013\u202f22:00** | **Nightlife** \u2013 optional bar/club (e.g., *Club Cabana*). | Drinks \u20b9300\u2011\u20b9600. Return to hotel by 22:30. |\n| **Day\u202f2 \u2013 South Goa Relaxation** | **08:00\u202f\u2013\u202f09:00** | **Breakfast** at hotel or *Brittany Caf\u00e9* (Colva). | \u20b9150\u2011\u20b9250. |\n| | **09:00\u202f\u2013\u202f10:30** | **Drive to Colva Beach** (\u2248\u202f45\u202fkm, 1\u202fh 15\u202fmin). | Scenic coastal road; stop for photos. |\n| | **10:30\u202f\u2013\u202f12:30** | **Colva & Benaulim Beaches** \u2013 sunbathing, optional dolphin\u2011watching boat (\u20b91,200 per person). |\n| | **12:30\u202f\u2013\u202f13:30** | **Lunch** at *Martin\u2019s Corner* (Colva) \u2013 Goan chicken xacuti. | \u20b9350\u2011\u20b9500. |\n| | **13:30\u202f\u2013\u202f15:00** | **Cabo de Rama Fort** \u2013 historic ruins & panoramic sea view. | 20\u202fkm from Colva (\u2248\u202f30\u202fmin). Entry free. |\n| | **15:00\u202f\u2013\u202f16:30** | **Palolem Beach** \u2013 calm waters, hammocks, coconut water. | 30\u202fkm from Cabo (\u2248\u202f45\u202fmin). |\n| | **16:30\u202f\u2013\u202f18:00** | **Kayaking in the backwaters** (optional) \u2013 \u20b9800 per person. |\n| | **18:00\u202f\u2013\u202f19:30** | **Sunset at Agonda Beach** \u2013 quieter spot, perfect for photos. |\n| | **19:30\u202f\u2013\u202f21:00** | **Dinner** at *Martin\u2019s Corner* (Agonda) or *Ritz Caf\u00e9* \u2013 Goan fish curry & rice. | \u20b9350\u2011\u20b9600. |\n| | **21:00\u202f\u2013\u202f22:30** | **Return to Panaji** (\u2248\u202f1\u202fh 15\u202fmin) \u2013 pack, relax. | If you have a late flight/train, stay near the airport; otherwise, enjoy a nightcap at a local bar. |\n\n### Quick \u201cWhat\u2011to\u2011Pack\u201d Checklist\n- Light cotton clothing, swimwear, flip\u2011flops + comfortable shoes for forts.\n- Sunscreen (SPF\u202f30+), sunglasses, hat.\n- Small day\u2011backpack, reusable water bottle.\n- Power bank, universal plug adapter (India uses Type\u202fC/D/M, 230\u202fV).\n- Cash (\u20b9) for small vendors; most places accept cards, but keep \u20b92,000\u2011\u20b93,000 handy for markets.\n\n---\n\n## 2\ufe0f\u20e3 HOTEL RECOMMENDATIONS  \n\n| Category | Hotel (Location) | Approx. Rate (per night, INR) | Key Amenities | Why It Fits the Itinerary |\n|----------|------------------|------------------------------|----------------|---------------------------|\n| **Budget** | **Casa De Goa \u2013 Heritage Home** (Panaji) | **\u20b92,500 \u2013 3,200** (double occupancy) | Free Wi\u2011Fi, rooftop garden, air\u2011conditioned rooms, breakfast included. | Central location \u2192 easy to reach North & South Goa; walking distance to Miramar Beach. |\n| **Mid\u2011Range** | **The Flora Residency** (Candolim, North Goa) | **\u20b95,500 \u2013 7,000** | Outdoor pool, sea\u2011view rooms, on\u2011site restaurant, 24\u202fh front desk. | Near Calangute/Baga \u2192 saves travel time on Day\u202f1; still a short drive to South Goa on Day\u202f2. |\n| **Luxury** | **Taj Exotica Resort & Spa** (Benaulim, South Goa) | **\u20b918,000 \u2013 22,000** | Private beach, spa, multiple dining venues, infinity pool, concierge. | Perfect if you want a pampered night after Day\u202f1 and a relaxed Day\u202f2 on the South\u2011Goa coast. |\n\n> **Tip:** All three hotels can be booked via major portals (Booking.com, MakeMyTrip) with free cancellation up to 24\u202fh before check\u2011in. Prices shown are for **standard double rooms** in the high\u2011season (Oct\u2011Mar). Off\u2011season rates can be 30\u201140\u202f% lower.\n\n---\n\n## 3\ufe0f\u20e3 BUDGET CALCULATOR (INR)\n\n| Item | Cost (\u20b9) | Details |\n|------|----------|---------|\n| **Accommodation (2 nights)** | **Budget**: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b92,800 = **\u20b95,600**<br>**Mid\u2011Range**: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b96,200 = **\u20b912,400**<br>**Luxury**: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b920,000 = **\u20b940,000** | Rates are average per night (incl. taxes). |\n| **Food & Drinks** (2\u202fdays) | Breakfast: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b9200 = \u20b9400<br>Lunch: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b9450 = \u20b9900<br>Dinner: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b9750 = \u20b91,500<br>Snacks/Drinks: \u20b9600 | **Total** \u2248 **\u20b93,400** per person (mid\u2011range). |\n| **Local Transport** | Scooter rental (\u20b9350\u202f/\u202fday) \u00d7\u202f2 = \u20b9700<br>Fuel (\u2248\u202f30\u202fkm\u202f/\u202fday, \u20b990\u202f/\u202fL, 30\u202fL total) = \u20b92,700<br>Occasional auto\u2011rickshaw/taxi for night out = \u20b9500 | **Total** \u2248 **\u20b93,900** |\n| **Attraction Fees & Activities** | Fort Aguada lighthouse \u20b920<br>Water\u2011sports (choose one) \u20b91,000<br>Dolphin\u2011watch boat (optional) \u20b91,200<br>Kayaking (optional) \u20b9800<br>Misc (market souvenirs) \u20b91,000 | **Total (with optional activities)** \u2248 **\u20b94,020** |\n| **Miscellaneous** (tips, laundry, emergency cash) | \u20b91,000 |\n| **Grand Total (per person)** | **Budget\u2011Hotel combo**: \u20b95,600 + \u20b93,400 + \u20b93,900 + \u20b94,020 + \u20b91,000 \u2248 **\u20b917,920**<br>**Mid\u2011Range combo**: \u20b912,400 + \u20b93,400 + \u20b93,900 + \u20b94,020 + \u20b91,000 \u2248 **\u20b924,720**<br>**Luxury combo**: \u20b940,000 + \u20b93,400 + \u20b93,900 + \u20b94,020 + \u20b91,000 \u2248 **\u20b952,320** |\n| **Your Target** | **\u20b950,000** | The **mid\u2011range** option comfortably fits under \u20b950k. If you prefer a splurge, you can stay at the luxury resort for one night and a budget hotel the other night to stay within the limit. |\n\n### Sample \u201cMid\u2011Range\u201d Cost Breakdown (most realistic for \u20b950k)\n\n| Category | Amount (\u20b9) |\n|----------|------------|\n| Hotel (2 nights, The Flora Residency) | 12,400 |\n| Food & Drinks | 3,400 |\n| Transport (scooter + fuel + occasional taxi) | 3,900 |\n| Activities & Entry Fees | 4,020 |\n| Miscellaneous | 1,000 |\n| **Total** | **\u20b924,720** (\u2248\u202f\u20b912,360 per day) |\n\n*If you are traveling with a companion and sharing a room, the accommodation cost halves, bringing the per\u2011person total to **\u2248\u202f\u20b913,000** \u2013 well under your \u20b950k budget, leaving plenty for extra shopping or a spa treatment.*\n\n---\n\n## 4\ufe0f\u20e3 PRACTICAL TRAVEL TIPS & RECOMMENDATIONS  \n\n| Topic | Advice |\n|-------|--------|\n| **Best Time to Visit** | **Oct\u202f\u2013\u202fMar** (cool, dry, peak tourist season). Avoid monsoon (Jun\u2011Sep) unless you love rain\u2011soaked scenery. |\n| **Getting to Goa** | Fly into **Dabolim Airport (GOI)** \u2013 cheap flights from major Indian metros. From the airport, take a prepaid taxi (\u2248\u202f\u20b9800) to your hotel or pick up your pre\u2011booked scooter at the airport kiosk. |\n| **Getting Around** | **Rent a scooter** (\u20b9300\u2011\u20b9400\u202f/\u202fday). It\u2019s the most flexible, cheap, and popular way to explore both coasts. Carry a valid driving licence (Indian or International). For longer distances (e.g., Panaji \u2192 South Goa), a **private cab** (\u20b92,500\u2011\u20b93,000) is comfortable. |\n| **Safety** | Goa is tourist\u2011friendly. Keep an eye on your belongings on crowded beaches and markets. Avoid isolated beaches after dark unless you\u2019re with a group. Drink bottled water. |\n| **Currency** | ATMs are plentiful in Panaji, Calangute, and South Goa. Keep some cash for small stalls; most restaurants accept cards. |\n| **Connectivity** | 4G coverage is excellent. Buy a local SIM (Jio, Airtel) at the airport for ~\u20b9200 with 2\u202fGB data. |\n| **Cultural Etiquette** | Dress modestly when visiting churches or temples (cover shoulders/knees). Remove shoes before entering places of worship. Tipping 5\u201110\u202f% in restaurants is appreciated. |\n| **Must\u2011Try Foods** | *Goan fish curry*, *prawn balch\u00e3o*, *bebinca* (dessert), *feni* (local cashew spirit) \u2013 try in reputable eateries. |\n| **Eco\u2011Friendly Tips** | Use refillable water bottles, avoid single\u2011use plastics, and respect beach clean\u2011up signs. |\n\n---\n\n## 5\ufe0f\u20e3 QUICK \u201cTO\u2011DO\u201d CHECKLIST (Before You Leave)\n\n1. **Book flights** (arrive night before Day\u202f1 or early morning).  \n2. **Reserve hotel** (choose budget/mid\u2011range/luxury).  \n3. **Pre\u2011book scooter** (many hotels arrange it; otherwise, rent at the airport).  \n4. **Download offline maps** (Google Maps offline for Panaji\u2011Baga\u2011Colva corridor).  \n5. **Pack** (light clothing, sunscreen, hat, reusable bottle, basic meds).  \n6. **Arrange travel insurance** (covers medical emergencies, lost luggage).  \n7. **Notify bank** of travel dates (to avoid card blocks).  \n\n---\n\n### \ud83c\udf89 Ready to Go!\n\n- **If you want a comfortable, hassle\u2011free trip** \u2013 go with the **mid\u2011range hotel** (The Flora Residency) and follow the itinerary above.  \n- **If you\u2019re traveling solo or with a friend** \u2013 share a budget hotel and you\u2019ll stay well under \u20b920k total, leaving plenty for extra activities or souvenirs.  \n- **If you crave a splurge** \u2013 spend one night at **Taj Exotica** (South Goa) and the other night at a budget stay; you\u2019ll still land close to the \u20b950k ceiling.\n\nEnjoy the sun, sea, and spice\u2011laden flavors of Goa! \ud83c\udf1e\ud83c\udfd6\ufe0f\ud83d\udea4 Feel free to ask for any tweaks (e.g., vegetarian food options, alternative beaches, or a different travel date) and I\u2019ll fine\u2011tune the plan for you. Happy travels!", "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": null, "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": null, "reasoning": "We need to produce a two-day itinerary for Goa, with budget of 50,000 (presumably INR). Provide day-by-day itinerary, hotel suggestions (budget, mid-range, luxury) with approximate prices, budget calculator with accommodation, food, transport, attractions, total. Also travel tips. Need to be realistic. Provide time estimates. Use Indian rupees. Provide suggestions for transport (rental scooter, taxis). Provide food costs. Provide entry fees for attractions. Ensure total within 50,000. Provide options for different budgets. Also note that 50k for two days is generous; can include mid-range. Provide breakdown.\n\nLet's craft answer."}}], "created": 1771565631, "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b", "object": "chat.completion", "service_tier": "on_demand", "system_fingerprint": "fp_626f3fc5e0", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 3268, "prompt_tokens": 272, "total_tokens": 3540, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 134, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": null, "queue_time": 0.046563914, "prompt_time": 0.016382316, "completion_time": 7.00471659, "total_time": 7.021098906}, "usage_breakdown": null, "x_groq": {"id": "req_01khwrmbh4enmtpyjc33svyh5p", "seed": 1178770028}}, "prompt_tokens": 272, "completion_tokens": 3268, "agent_id": "Travel_Planner_70dc2a6d-4783-4b71-9848-18e054b71814/70dc2a6d-4783-4b71-9848-18e054b71814"}
2026-02-20 11:03:53 - INFO - 405 -Publishing message of type GroupChatMessage to all subscribers: {'message': TextMessage(id='9cdf2695-e7e6-4d4e-8c68-da6e42d570ff', source='Travel_Planner', models_usage=RequestUsage(prompt_tokens=272, completion_tokens=3268), metadata={}, created_at=datetime.datetime(2026, 2, 20, 5, 33, 53, 901023, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), content='## 2\u2011Day Goa Getaway – INR\u202f50,000 (\u2248\u202f\u20b925,000 per day)\n\nBelow is a **ready\u2011to\u2011use** plan that covers:\n\n* **Day\u2011by\u2011day itinerary** (morning\u202f/\u202fafternoon\u202f/\u202fevening) with realistic travel times.  \n* **Hotel recommendations** for three budget tiers (budget, mid\u2011range, luxury) with per\u2011night rates.  \n* **Itemised budget calculator** (accommodation, food, transport, entry fees, misc).  \n* **Practical travel tips** (how to move around, what to pack, safety, best time to visit).\n\n---\n\n## 1\ufe0f\u20e3 DAY\u2011BY\u2011DAY ITINERARY  \n\n> **Assumptions** – You’ll arrive in Goa by flight or train the night before Day\u202f1 (or early on Day\u202f1). The plan starts from **Panaji (the capital)**, which is a convenient base for both North and South Goa. All times are approximate and can be shifted by a few minutes depending on traffic and personal pace.\n\n| Day | Time | Activity | Details & Travel Time |\n|-----|------|----------|-----------------------|\n| **Day\u202f1 – North Goa Highlights** | **08:00\u202f–\u202f09:00** | **Breakfast** at the hotel or a local café (e.g., *Cafe Bodega*). | Typical Indian breakfast: idli\u2011vada, poha, fresh juice – \u20b9150\u2011\u20b9250. |\n| | **09:00\u202f–\u202f10:30** | **Fort Aguada & Lighthouse** | 5\u202fkm from Panaji (\u2248\u202f15\u202fmin by scooter). Entry free; small fee for lighthouse (\u20b920). |\n| | **10:30\u202f–\u202f12:00** | **Sinquerim Beach** – quick dip or sunrise walk. | 2\u202fkm from Fort Aguada (\u2248\u202f5\u202fmin). |\n| | **12:00\u202f–\u202f13:30** | **Lunch** at *Martin’s Corner* (Baga) – Goan seafood thali. | \u20b9350\u2011\u20b9500. |\n| | **13:30\u202f–\u202f15:30** | **Calangute & Baga Beaches** – water\u2011sports (optional jet\u2011ski, parasailing). | Activity cost: \u20b9800\u2011\u20b91,200 per person (choose one). |\n| | **15:30\u202f–\u202f16:30** | **Anjuna Flea Market** (Wednesday\u2011Saturday) – shop for souvenirs, jewellery, handicrafts. | No entry fee; budget \u20b9500\u2011\u20b91,000 for shopping. |\n| | **16:30\u202f–\u202f18:00** | **Chapora Fort** – sunset view over Vagator Beach. | 6\u202fkm from Anjuna (\u2248\u202f15\u202fmin). Entry free. |\n| | **18:00\u202f–\u202f20:00** | **Dinner** at *Thalassa* (Vagator) – Greek\u2011Goan fusion, great sunset vibe. | \u20b9600\u2011\u20b9900 per person. |\n| | **20:00\u202f–\u202f22:00** | **Nightlife** – optional bar/club (e.g., *Club Cabana*). | Drinks \u20b9300\u2011\u20b9600. Return to hotel by 22:30. |\n| **Day\u202f2 – South Goa Relaxation** | **08:00\u202f–\u202f09:00** | **Breakfast** at hotel or *Brittany Café* (Colva). | \u20b9150\u2011\u20b9250. |\n| | **09:00\u202f–\u202f10:30** | **Drive to Colva Beach** (\u2248\u202f45\u202fkm, 1\u202fh 15\u202fmin). | Scenic coastal road; stop for photos. |\n| | **10:30\u202f–\u202f12:30** | **Colva & Benaulim Beaches** – sunbathing, optional dolphin\u2011watching boat (\u20b91,200 per person). |\n| | **12:30\u202f–\u202f13:30** | **Lunch** at *Martin’s Corner* (Colva) – Goan chicken xacuti. | \u20b9350\u2011\u20b9500. |\n| | **13:30\u202f–\u202f15:00** | **Cabo de Rama Fort** – historic ruins & panoramic sea view. | 20\u202fkm from Colva (\u2248\u202f30\u202fmin). Entry free. |\n| | **15:00\u202f–\u202f16:30** | **Palolem Beach** – calm waters, hammocks, coconut water. | 30\u202fkm from Cabo (\u2248\u202f45\u202fmin). |\n| | **16:30\u202f–\u202f18:00** | **Kayaking in the backwaters** (optional) – \u20b9800 per person. |\n| | **18:00\u202f–\u202f19:30** | **Sunset at Agonda Beach** – quieter spot, perfect for photos. |\n| | **19:30\u202f–\u202f21:00** | **Dinner** at *Martin’s Corner* (Agonda) or *Ritz Café* – Goan fish curry & rice. | \u20b9350\u2011\u20b9600. |\n| | **21:00\u202f–\u202f22:30** | **Return to Panaji** (\u2248\u202f1\u202fh 15\u202fmin) – pack, relax. | If you have a late flight/train, stay near the airport; otherwise, enjoy a nightcap at a local bar. |\n\n### Quick “What\u2011to\u2011Pack” Checklist\n- Light cotton clothing, swimwear, flip\u2011flops + comfortable shoes for forts.\n- Sunscreen (SPF\u202f30+), sunglasses, hat.\n- Small day\u2011backpack, reusable water bottle.\n- Power bank, universal plug adapter (India uses Type\u202fC/D/M, 230\u202fV).\n- Cash (\u20b9) for small vendors; most places accept cards, but keep \u20b92,000\u2011\u20b93,000 handy for markets.\n\n---\n\n## 2\ufe0f\u20e3 HOTEL RECOMMENDATIONS  \n\n| Category | Hotel (Location) | Approx. Rate (per night, INR) | Key Amenities | Why It Fits the Itinerary |\n|----------|------------------|------------------------------|----------------|---------------------------|\n| **Budget** | **Casa De Goa – Heritage Home** (Panaji) | **\u20b92,500 – 3,200** (double occupancy) | Free Wi\u2011Fi, rooftop garden, air\u2011conditioned rooms, breakfast included. | Central location \u2192 easy to reach North & South Goa; walking distance to Miramar Beach. |\n| **Mid\u2011Range** | **The Flora Residency** (Candolim, North Goa) | **\u20b95,500 – 7,000** | Outdoor pool, sea\u2011view rooms, on\u2011site restaurant, 24\u202fh front desk. | Near Calangute/Baga \u2192 saves travel time on Day\u202f1; still a short drive to South Goa on Day\u202f2. |\n| **Luxury** | **Taj Exotica Resort & Spa** (Benaulim, South Goa) | **\u20b918,000 – 22,000** | Private beach, spa, multiple dining venues, infinity pool, concierge. | Perfect if you want a pampered night after Day\u202f1 and a relaxed Day\u202f2 on the South\u2011Goa coast. |\n\n> **Tip:** All three hotels can be booked via major portals (Booking.com, MakeMyTrip) with free cancellation up to 24\u202fh before check\u2011in. Prices shown are for **standard double rooms** in the high\u2011season (Oct\u2011Mar). Off\u2011season rates can be 30\u201140\u202f% lower.\n\n---\n\n## 3\ufe0f\u20e3 BUDGET CALCULATOR (INR)\n\n| Item | Cost (\u20b9) | Details |\n|------|----------|---------|\n| **Accommodation (2 nights)** | **Budget**: 2\u202f×\u202f\u20b92,800 = **\u20b95,600**<br>**Mid\u2011Range**: 2\u202f×\u202f\u20b96,200 = **\u20b912,400**<br>**Luxury**: 2\u202f×\u202f\u20b920,000 = **\u20b940,000** | Rates are average per night (incl. taxes). |\n| **Food & Drinks** (2\u202fdays) | Breakfast: 2\u202f×\u202f\u20b9200 = \u20b9400<br>Lunch: 2\u202f×\u202f\u20b9450 = \u20b9900<br>Dinner: 2\u202f×\u202f\u20b9750 = \u20b91,500<br>Snacks/Drinks: \u20b9600 | **Total** \u2248 **\u20b93,400** per person (mid\u2011range). |\n| **Local Transport** | Scooter rental (\u20b9350\u202f/\u202fday) ×\u202f2 = \u20b9700<br>Fuel (\u2248\u202f30\u202fkm\u202f/\u202fday, \u20b990\u202f/\u202fL, 30\u202fL total) = \u20b92,700<br>Occasional auto\u2011rickshaw/taxi for night out = \u20b9500 | **Total** \u2248 **\u20b93,900** |\n| **Attraction Fees & Activities** | Fort Aguada lighthouse \u20b920<br>Water\u2011sports (choose one) \u20b91,000<br>Dolphin\u2011watch boat (optional) \u20b91,200<br>Kayaking (optional) \u20b9800<br>Misc (market souvenirs) \u20b91,000 | **Total (with optional activities)** \u2248 **\u20b94,020** |\n| **Miscellaneous** (tips, laundry, emergency cash) | \u20b91,000 |\n| **Grand Total (per person)** | **Budget\u2011Hotel combo**: \u20b95,600 + \u20b93,400 + \u20b93,900 + \u20b94,020 + \u20b91,000 \u2248 **\u20b917,920**<br>**Mid\u2011Range combo**: \u20b912,400 + \u20b93,400 + \u20b93,900 + \u20b94,020 + \u20b91,000 \u2248 **\u20b924,720**<br>**Luxury combo**: \u20b940,000 + \u20b93,400 + \u20b93,900 + \u20b94,020 + \u20b91,000 \u2248 **\u20b952,320** |\n| **Your Target** | **\u20b950,000** | The **mid\u2011range** option comfortably fits under \u20b950k. If you prefer a splurge, you can stay at the luxury resort for one night and a budget hotel the other night to stay within the limit. |\n\n### Sample “Mid\u2011Range” Cost Breakdown (most realistic for \u20b950k)\n\n| Category | Amount (\u20b9) |\n|----------|------------|\n| Hotel (2 nights, The Flora Residency) | 12,400 |\n| Food & Drinks | 3,400 |\n| Transport (scooter + fuel + occasional taxi) | 3,900 |\n| Activities & Entry Fees | 4,020 |\n| Miscellaneous | 1,000 |\n| **Total** | **\u20b924,720** (\u2248\u202f\u20b912,360 per day) |\n\n*If you are traveling with a companion and sharing a room, the accommodation cost halves, bringing the per\u2011person total to **\u2248\u202f\u20b913,000** – well under your \u20b950k budget, leaving plenty for extra shopping or a spa treatment.*\n\n---\n\n## 4\ufe0f\u20e3 PRACTICAL TRAVEL TIPS & RECOMMENDATIONS  \n\n| Topic | Advice |\n|-------|--------|\n| **Best Time to Visit** | **Oct\u202f–\u202fMar** (cool, dry, peak tourist season). Avoid monsoon (Jun\u2011Sep) unless you love rain\u2011soaked scenery. |\n| **Getting to Goa** | Fly into **Dabolim Airport (GOI)** – cheap flights from major Indian metros. From the airport, take a prepaid taxi (\u2248\u202f\u20b9800) to your hotel or pick up your pre\u2011booked scooter at the airport kiosk. |\n| **Getting Around** | **Rent a scooter** (\u20b9300\u2011\u20b9400\u202f/\u202fday). It’s the most flexible, cheap, and popular way to explore both coasts. Carry a valid driving licence (Indian or International). For longer distances (e.g., Panaji \u2192 South Goa), a **private cab** (\u20b92,500\u2011\u20b93,000) is comfortable. |\n| **Safety** | Goa is tourist\u2011friendly. Keep an eye on your belongings on crowded beaches and markets. Avoid isolated beaches after dark unless you’re with a group. Drink bottled water. |\n| **Currency** | ATMs are plentiful in Panaji, Calangute, and South Goa. Keep some cash for small stalls; most restaurants accept cards. |\n| **Connectivity** | 4G coverage is excellent. Buy a local SIM (Jio, Airtel) at the airport for ~\u20b9200 with 2\u202fGB data. |\n| **Cultural Etiquette** | Dress modestly when visiting churches or temples (cover shoulders/knees). Remove shoes before entering places of worship. Tipping 5\u201110\u202f% in restaurants is appreciated. |\n| **Must\u2011Try Foods** | *Goan fish curry*, *prawn balchăo*, *bebinca* (dessert), *feni* (local cashew spirit) – try in reputable eateries. |\n| **Eco\u2011Friendly Tips** | Use refillable water bottles, avoid single\u2011use plastics, and respect beach clean\u2011up signs. |\n\n---\n\n## 5\ufe0f\u20e3 QUICK “TO\u2011DO” CHECKLIST (Before You Leave)\n\n1. **Book flights** (arrive night before Day\u202f1 or early morning).  \n2. **Reserve hotel** (choose budget/mid\u2011range/luxury).  \n3. **Pre\u2011book scooter** (many hotels arrange it; otherwise, rent at the airport).  \n4. **Download offline maps** (Google Maps offline for Panaji\u2011Baga\u2011Colva corridor).  \n5. **Pack** (light clothing, sunscreen, hat, reusable bottle, basic meds).  \n6. **Arrange travel insurance** (covers medical emergencies, lost luggage).  \n7. **Notify bank** of travel dates (to avoid card blocks).  \n\n---\n\n### \U0001f389 Ready to Go!\n\n- **If you want a comfortable, hassle\u2011free trip** – go with the **mid\u2011range hotel** (The Flora Residency) and follow the itinerary above.  \n- **If you’re traveling solo or with a friend** – share a budget hotel and you’ll stay well under \u20b920k total, leaving plenty for extra activities or souvenirs.  \n- **If you crave a splurge** – spend one night at **Taj Exotica** (South Goa) and the other night at a budget stay; you’ll still land close to the \u20b950k ceiling.\n\nEnjoy the sun, sea, and spice\u2011laden flavors of Goa! \U0001f31e\U0001f3d6\ufe0f\U0001f6a4 Feel free to ask for any tweaks (e.g., vegetarian food options, alternative beaches, or a different travel date) and I’ll fine\u2011tune the plan for you. Happy travels!', type='TextMessage')}
2026-02-20 11:03:53 - INFO - 410 -{"payload": "{\"message\":{\"id\":\"9cdf2695-e7e6-4d4e-8c68-da6e42d570ff\",\"source\":\"Travel_Planner\",\"models_usage\":{\"prompt_tokens\":272,\"completion_tokens\":3268},\"metadata\":{},\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T05:33:53.901023Z\",\"content\":\"## 2\u2011Day Goa Getaway \u2013 INR\u202f50,000 (\u2248\u202f\u20b925,000 per day)\\n\\nBelow is a **ready\u2011to\u2011use** plan that covers:\\n\\n* **Day\u2011by\u2011day itinerary** (morning\u202f/\u202fafternoon\u202f/\u202fevening) with realistic travel times.  \\n* **Hotel recommendations** for three budget tiers (budget, mid\u2011range, luxury) with per\u2011night rates.  \\n* **Itemised budget calculator** (accommodation, food, transport, entry fees, misc).  \\n* **Practical travel tips** (how to move around, what to pack, safety, best time to visit).\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1\ufe0f\u20e3 DAY\u2011BY\u2011DAY ITINERARY  \\n\\n> **Assumptions** \u2013 You\u2019ll arrive in Goa by flight or train the night before Day\u202f1 (or early on Day\u202f1). The plan starts from **Panaji (the capital)**, which is a convenient base for both North and South Goa. All times are approximate and can be shifted by a few minutes depending on traffic and personal pace.\\n\\n| Day | Time | Activity | Details & Travel Time |\\n|-----|------|----------|-----------------------|\\n| **Day\u202f1 \u2013 North Goa Highlights** | **08:00\u202f\u2013\u202f09:00** | **Breakfast** at the hotel or a local caf\u00e9 (e.g., *Cafe Bodega*). | Typical Indian breakfast: idli\u2011vada, poha, fresh juice \u2013 \u20b9150\u2011\u20b9250. |\\n| | **09:00\u202f\u2013\u202f10:30** | **Fort Aguada & Lighthouse** | 5\u202fkm from Panaji (\u2248\u202f15\u202fmin by scooter). Entry free; small fee for lighthouse (\u20b920). |\\n| | **10:30\u202f\u2013\u202f12:00** | **Sinquerim Beach** \u2013 quick dip or sunrise walk. | 2\u202fkm from Fort Aguada (\u2248\u202f5\u202fmin). |\\n| | **12:00\u202f\u2013\u202f13:30** | **Lunch** at *Martin\u2019s Corner* (Baga) \u2013 Goan seafood thali. | \u20b9350\u2011\u20b9500. |\\n| | **13:30\u202f\u2013\u202f15:30** | **Calangute & Baga Beaches** \u2013 water\u2011sports (optional jet\u2011ski, parasailing). | Activity cost: \u20b9800\u2011\u20b91,200 per person (choose one). |\\n| | **15:30\u202f\u2013\u202f16:30** | **Anjuna Flea Market** (Wednesday\u2011Saturday) \u2013 shop for souvenirs, jewellery, handicrafts. | No entry fee; budget \u20b9500\u2011\u20b91,000 for shopping. |\\n| | **16:30\u202f\u2013\u202f18:00** | **Chapora Fort** \u2013 sunset view over Vagator Beach. | 6\u202fkm from Anjuna (\u2248\u202f15\u202fmin). Entry free. |\\n| | **18:00\u202f\u2013\u202f20:00** | **Dinner** at *Thalassa* (Vagator) \u2013 Greek\u2011Goan fusion, great sunset vibe. | \u20b9600\u2011\u20b9900 per person. |\\n| | **20:00\u202f\u2013\u202f22:00** | **Nightlife** \u2013 optional bar/club (e.g., *Club Cabana*). | Drinks \u20b9300\u2011\u20b9600. Return to hotel by 22:30. |\\n| **Day\u202f2 \u2013 South Goa Relaxation** | **08:00\u202f\u2013\u202f09:00** | **Breakfast** at hotel or *Brittany Caf\u00e9* (Colva). | \u20b9150\u2011\u20b9250. |\\n| | **09:00\u202f\u2013\u202f10:30** | **Drive to Colva Beach** (\u2248\u202f45\u202fkm, 1\u202fh 15\u202fmin). | Scenic coastal road; stop for photos. |\\n| | **10:30\u202f\u2013\u202f12:30** | **Colva & Benaulim Beaches** \u2013 sunbathing, optional dolphin\u2011watching boat (\u20b91,200 per person). |\\n| | **12:30\u202f\u2013\u202f13:30** | **Lunch** at *Martin\u2019s Corner* (Colva) \u2013 Goan chicken xacuti. | \u20b9350\u2011\u20b9500. |\\n| | **13:30\u202f\u2013\u202f15:00** | **Cabo de Rama Fort** \u2013 historic ruins & panoramic sea view. | 20\u202fkm from Colva (\u2248\u202f30\u202fmin). Entry free. |\\n| | **15:00\u202f\u2013\u202f16:30** | **Palolem Beach** \u2013 calm waters, hammocks, coconut water. | 30\u202fkm from Cabo (\u2248\u202f45\u202fmin). |\\n| | **16:30\u202f\u2013\u202f18:00** | **Kayaking in the backwaters** (optional) \u2013 \u20b9800 per person. |\\n| | **18:00\u202f\u2013\u202f19:30** | **Sunset at Agonda Beach** \u2013 quieter spot, perfect for photos. |\\n| | **19:30\u202f\u2013\u202f21:00** | **Dinner** at *Martin\u2019s Corner* (Agonda) or *Ritz Caf\u00e9* \u2013 Goan fish curry & rice. | \u20b9350\u2011\u20b9600. |\\n| | **21:00\u202f\u2013\u202f22:30** | **Return to Panaji** (\u2248\u202f1\u202fh 15\u202fmin) \u2013 pack, relax. | If you have a late flight/train, stay near the airport; otherwise, enjoy a nightcap at a local bar. |\\n\\n### Quick \u201cWhat\u2011to\u2011Pack\u201d Checklist\\n- Light cotton clothing, swimwear, flip\u2011flops + comfortable shoes for forts.\\n- Sunscreen (SPF\u202f30+), sunglasses, hat.\\n- Small day\u2011backpack, reusable water bottle.\\n- Power bank, universal plug adapter (India uses Type\u202fC/D/M, 230\u202fV).\\n- Cash (\u20b9) for small vendors; most places accept cards, but keep \u20b92,000\u2011\u20b93,000 handy for markets.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2\ufe0f\u20e3 HOTEL RECOMMENDATIONS  \\n\\n| Category | Hotel (Location) | Approx. Rate (per night, INR) | Key Amenities | Why It Fits the Itinerary |\\n|----------|------------------|------------------------------|----------------|---------------------------|\\n| **Budget** | **Casa De Goa \u2013 Heritage Home** (Panaji) | **\u20b92,500 \u2013 3,200** (double occupancy) | Free Wi\u2011Fi, rooftop garden, air\u2011conditioned rooms, breakfast included. | Central location \u2192 easy to reach North & South Goa; walking distance to Miramar Beach. |\\n| **Mid\u2011Range** | **The Flora Residency** (Candolim, North Goa) | **\u20b95,500 \u2013 7,000** | Outdoor pool, sea\u2011view rooms, on\u2011site restaurant, 24\u202fh front desk. | Near Calangute/Baga \u2192 saves travel time on Day\u202f1; still a short drive to South Goa on Day\u202f2. |\\n| **Luxury** | **Taj Exotica Resort & Spa** (Benaulim, South Goa) | **\u20b918,000 \u2013 22,000** | Private beach, spa, multiple dining venues, infinity pool, concierge. | Perfect if you want a pampered night after Day\u202f1 and a relaxed Day\u202f2 on the South\u2011Goa coast. |\\n\\n> **Tip:** All three hotels can be booked via major portals (Booking.com, MakeMyTrip) with free cancellation up to 24\u202fh before check\u2011in. Prices shown are for **standard double rooms** in the high\u2011season (Oct\u2011Mar). Off\u2011season rates can be 30\u201140\u202f% lower.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3\ufe0f\u20e3 BUDGET CALCULATOR (INR)\\n\\n| Item | Cost (\u20b9) | Details |\\n|------|----------|---------|\\n| **Accommodation (2 nights)** | **Budget**: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b92,800 = **\u20b95,600**<br>**Mid\u2011Range**: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b96,200 = **\u20b912,400**<br>**Luxury**: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b920,000 = **\u20b940,000** | Rates are average per night (incl. taxes). |\\n| **Food & Drinks** (2\u202fdays) | Breakfast: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b9200 = \u20b9400<br>Lunch: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b9450 = \u20b9900<br>Dinner: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b9750 = \u20b91,500<br>Snacks/Drinks: \u20b9600 | **Total** \u2248 **\u20b93,400** per person (mid\u2011range). |\\n| **Local Transport** | Scooter rental (\u20b9350\u202f/\u202fday) \u00d7\u202f2 = \u20b9700<br>Fuel (\u2248\u202f30\u202fkm\u202f/\u202fday, \u20b990\u202f/\u202fL, 30\u202fL total) = \u20b92,700<br>Occasional auto\u2011rickshaw/taxi for night out = \u20b9500 | **Total** \u2248 **\u20b93,900** |\\n| **Attraction Fees & Activities** | Fort Aguada lighthouse \u20b920<br>Water\u2011sports (choose one) \u20b91,000<br>Dolphin\u2011watch boat (optional) \u20b91,200<br>Kayaking (optional) \u20b9800<br>Misc (market souvenirs) \u20b91,000 | **Total (with optional activities)** \u2248 **\u20b94,020** |\\n| **Miscellaneous** (tips, laundry, emergency cash) | \u20b91,000 |\\n| **Grand Total (per person)** | **Budget\u2011Hotel combo**: \u20b95,600 + \u20b93,400 + \u20b93,900 + \u20b94,020 + \u20b91,000 \u2248 **\u20b917,920**<br>**Mid\u2011Range combo**: \u20b912,400 + \u20b93,400 + \u20b93,900 + \u20b94,020 + \u20b91,000 \u2248 **\u20b924,720**<br>**Luxury combo**: \u20b940,000 + \u20b93,400 + \u20b93,900 + \u20b94,020 + \u20b91,000 \u2248 **\u20b952,320** |\\n| **Your Target** | **\u20b950,000** | The **mid\u2011range** option comfortably fits under \u20b950k. If you prefer a splurge, you can stay at the luxury resort for one night and a budget hotel the other night to stay within the limit. |\\n\\n### Sample \u201cMid\u2011Range\u201d Cost Breakdown (most realistic for \u20b950k)\\n\\n| Category | Amount (\u20b9) |\\n|----------|------------|\\n| Hotel (2 nights, The Flora Residency) | 12,400 |\\n| Food & Drinks | 3,400 |\\n| Transport (scooter + fuel + occasional taxi) | 3,900 |\\n| Activities & Entry Fees | 4,020 |\\n| Miscellaneous | 1,000 |\\n| **Total** | **\u20b924,720** (\u2248\u202f\u20b912,360 per day) |\\n\\n*If you are traveling with a companion and sharing a room, the accommodation cost halves, bringing the per\u2011person total to **\u2248\u202f\u20b913,000** \u2013 well under your \u20b950k budget, leaving plenty for extra shopping or a spa treatment.*\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4\ufe0f\u20e3 PRACTICAL TRAVEL TIPS & RECOMMENDATIONS  \\n\\n| Topic | Advice |\\n|-------|--------|\\n| **Best Time to Visit** | **Oct\u202f\u2013\u202fMar** (cool, dry, peak tourist season). Avoid monsoon (Jun\u2011Sep) unless you love rain\u2011soaked scenery. |\\n| **Getting to Goa** | Fly into **Dabolim Airport (GOI)** \u2013 cheap flights from major Indian metros. From the airport, take a prepaid taxi (\u2248\u202f\u20b9800) to your hotel or pick up your pre\u2011booked scooter at the airport kiosk. |\\n| **Getting Around** | **Rent a scooter** (\u20b9300\u2011\u20b9400\u202f/\u202fday). It\u2019s the most flexible, cheap, and popular way to explore both coasts. Carry a valid driving licence (Indian or International). For longer distances (e.g., Panaji \u2192 South Goa), a **private cab** (\u20b92,500\u2011\u20b93,000) is comfortable. |\\n| **Safety** | Goa is tourist\u2011friendly. Keep an eye on your belongings on crowded beaches and markets. Avoid isolated beaches after dark unless you\u2019re with a group. Drink bottled water. |\\n| **Currency** | ATMs are plentiful in Panaji, Calangute, and South Goa. Keep some cash for small stalls; most restaurants accept cards. |\\n| **Connectivity** | 4G coverage is excellent. Buy a local SIM (Jio, Airtel) at the airport for ~\u20b9200 with 2\u202fGB data. |\\n| **Cultural Etiquette** | Dress modestly when visiting churches or temples (cover shoulders/knees). Remove shoes before entering places of worship. Tipping 5\u201110\u202f% in restaurants is appreciated. |\\n| **Must\u2011Try Foods** | *Goan fish curry*, *prawn balch\u00e3o*, *bebinca* (dessert), *feni* (local cashew spirit) \u2013 try in reputable eateries. |\\n| **Eco\u2011Friendly Tips** | Use refillable water bottles, avoid single\u2011use plastics, and respect beach clean\u2011up signs. |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 5\ufe0f\u20e3 QUICK \u201cTO\u2011DO\u201d CHECKLIST (Before You Leave)\\n\\n1. **Book flights** (arrive night before Day\u202f1 or early morning).  \\n2. **Reserve hotel** (choose budget/mid\u2011range/luxury).  \\n3. **Pre\u2011book scooter** (many hotels arrange it; otherwise, rent at the airport).  \\n4. **Download offline maps** (Google Maps offline for Panaji\u2011Baga\u2011Colva corridor).  \\n5. **Pack** (light clothing, sunscreen, hat, reusable bottle, basic meds).  \\n6. **Arrange travel insurance** (covers medical emergencies, lost luggage).  \\n7. **Notify bank** of travel dates (to avoid card blocks).  \\n\\n---\\n\\n### \ud83c\udf89 Ready to Go!\\n\\n- **If you want a comfortable, hassle\u2011free trip** \u2013 go with the **mid\u2011range hotel** (The Flora Residency) and follow the itinerary above.  \\n- **If you\u2019re traveling solo or with a friend** \u2013 share a budget hotel and you\u2019ll stay well under \u20b920k total, leaving plenty for extra activities or souvenirs.  \\n- **If you crave a splurge** \u2013 spend one night at **Taj Exotica** (South Goa) and the other night at a budget stay; you\u2019ll still land close to the \u20b950k ceiling.\\n\\nEnjoy the sun, sea, and spice\u2011laden flavors of Goa! \ud83c\udf1e\ud83c\udfd6\ufe0f\ud83d\udea4 Feel free to ask for any tweaks (e.g., vegetarian food options, alternative beaches, or a different travel date) and I\u2019ll fine\u2011tune the plan for you. Happy travels!\",\"type\":\"TextMessage\"}}", "sender": "Travel_Planner_70dc2a6d-4783-4b71-9848-18e054b71814/70dc2a6d-4783-4b71-9848-18e054b71814", "receiver": "output_topic_70dc2a6d-4783-4b71-9848-18e054b71814/70dc2a6d-4783-4b71-9848-18e054b71814", "kind": "MessageKind.PUBLISH", "delivery_stage": "DeliveryStage.SEND", "type": "Message"}
