ing\nimport requests\n\n# Assuming the exception class lives in a separate module\nfrom ..exceptions import HolidayAgentException\n\ndef get_route(origin, destination, api_key):\n    url = (\n        \"https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/directions/json\"\n        f\"?origin={origin}&destination={destination}&key={api_key}\"\n    )\n    response = requests.get(url, timeout=10)\n\n    if response.status_code != 200:\n        # Provide a helpful detail string\n        raise HolidayAgentException(\n            \"Google Maps request failed\",\n            f\"HTTP {response.status_code}: {response.text}\"\n        )\n\n    data = response.json()\n    if data.get(\"status\") != \"OK\":\n        # Another possible failure point\n        raise HolidayAgentException(\n            \"Google Maps API returned an error\",\n            f\"API status: {data.get('status')}, info: {data.get('error_message')}\"\n        )\n\n    # Normal return\n    return data[\"routes\"][0][\"overview_polyline\"][\"points\"]\n```\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\ude4b\u200d\u2640\ufe0f Need more help?\n\n* If you\u2019re not sure where the `HolidayAgentException` class is defined, let me know and I can walk you through locating it.  \n* If the error persists after adding the second argument, share the updated traceback and I\u2019ll dig deeper.  \n* Want a quick unit\u2011test snippet to verify the function works after the fix? I can provide that too.\n\nJust reply with the part of the code you\u2019re stuck on, and we\u2019ll get it running smoothly! \ud83d\ude80", "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": null, "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": null, "reasoning": "The user reports an error in a python script. As a Travel Planner assistant, we need to respond appropriately. The user likely expects help troubleshooting the error. We should explain the error: HolidayAgentException __init__ missing argument. Provide possible fix: define default argument or pass error_detail. Suggest 