 the class definition** | Search for `class HolidayAgentException` (likely in a common `exceptions.py` file). | Confirm the signature (`error_message, error_detail`). |\\n| **4\ufe0f\u20e3 Apply a fix** | Either add the missing argument at the raise site **or** give the class a default value. | Resolves the `TypeError`. |\\n| **5\ufe0f\u20e3 Run a quick test** | Execute the script (or the function that calls it) with a known good API key. | Verify that the exception is no longer raised unintentionally. |\\n| **6\ufe0f\u20e3 Add logging (optional)** | Insert `logging.error(...)` before raising, to capture the full context. | Makes future debugging easier. |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\udccc Example \u2013 Full corrected snippet\\n\\n```python\\nimport logging\\nimport requests\\n\\n# Assuming the exception class lives in a separate module\\nfrom ..exceptions import HolidayAgentException\\n\\ndef get_route(origin, destination, api_key):\\n    url = (\\n        \\\"https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/directions/json\\\"\\n        f\\\"?origin={origin}&destination={destination}&key={api_key}\\\"\\n    )\\n    response = requests.get(url, timeout=10)\\n\\n    if response.status_code != 200:\\n        # Provide a helpful detail string\\n        raise HolidayAgentException(\\n            \\\"Google Maps request failed\\\",\\n            f\\\"HTTP {response.status_code}: {response.text}\\\"\\n        )\\n\\n    data = response.json()\\n    if data.get(\\\"status\\\") != \\\"OK\\\":\\n        # Another possible failure point\\n        raise HolidayAgentException(\\n            \\\"Google Maps API returned an error\\\",\\n            f\\\"API status: {data.get('status')}, info: {data.get('error_message')}\\\"\\n        )\\n\\n    # Normal return\\n    return data[\\\"routes\\\"][0][\\\"overview_polyline\\\"][\\\"points\\\"]\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude4b\u200d\u2640\ufe0f Need more help?\\n\\n* If you\u2019re not sure where the `HolidayAgentException` class is defined, let me know and I can walk you through locating it.  \\n* If the error persists after adding the second argument, share the updated traceback and I\u2019ll dig deeper.  \\n* Want a quick unit\u2011test snippet to verify the function works after the fix? I can provide that too.\\n\\nJust reply with the part of the code you\u2019re stuck on, and we\u2019ll get it running smoothly! \ud83d\ude80\",\"type\":\"TextMessage\"},\"inner_messages\":[]},\"name\":\"Travel_Planner\"}", "sender": "Travel_Planner_70dc2a6d-4783-4b71-9848-18e054b71814/70dc2a6d-4783-4b71-9848-18e054b71814", "receiver": null, "kind": "MessageKind.PUBLISH", "delivery_stage": "DeliveryStage.DELIVER", "type": "Message"}
