2026-02-20 11:05:04 - INFO - 716 -{"tools": [{"type": "function", "function": {"name": "tavily_tool", "description": " Tavily tool to search on web  related to the hotel, destination, activities, and other travel-related information.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"query": {"description": "query", "title": "Query", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["query"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "google_map_tool", "description": " Google Map tool to get distance and duration between source and destination.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"source": {"description": "source", "title": "Source", "type": "string"}, "destination": {"description": "destination", "title": "Destination", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["source", "destination"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "serper_tool", "description": " Serper tool to search on web  related to the hotel availability and other travel-related information.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"query": {"description": "query", "title": "Query", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["query"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "You are a meticulous Travel Research Validator who verifies and fact-checks travel itineraries.\n\nYour role is to validate the Travel Planner's itinerary using the following tools:\n\n1. Google Maps Tool (google_map_tool):\n   - Verify distances between locations (source to destination)\n   - Check realistic travel times between attractions\n   - Validate transportation feasibility\n   - Calculate driving/transit distances\n\n2. Tavily Tool (tavily_tool):\n   - Search for famous tourist spots and verify their existence\n   - Find current information about attractions\n   - Verify opening hours and seasonal availability\n   - Check for any travel advisories or updates\n\n3. Serper Tool (serper_tool):\n   - Verify real-time hotel availability\n   - Check current hotel prices and ratings\n   - Validate accommodation options suggested by planner\n   - Search for recent reviews and recommendations\n\nValidation checklist:\n- Are the attractions real and currently accessible?\n- Are travel times between locations realistic?\n- Are hotel suggestions available and prices accurate?\n- Is the daily schedule feasible (not too packed)?\n- Are cost estimates reasonable and up-to-date?\n- Are there any missing important details?\n\nFinal decision:\nIf the itinerary looks good and all validations pass, say \"APPROVE\".\nOtherwise, suggest specific corrections with evidence from your research.", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "I want to two day trip to goa with the budget of 50000. Can you help me plan it?"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Travel_Planner", "content": "## 2\u2011Day Goa Getaway \u2013 INR\u202f50,000 (\u2248\u202f\u20b925,000 per day)\n\nBelow is a **ready\u2011to\u2011use** plan that covers:\n\n* **Day\u2011by\u2011day itinerary** (morning\u202f/\u202fafternoon\u202f/\u202fevening) with realistic travel times.  \n* **Hotel recommendations** for three budget tiers (budget, mid\u2011range, luxury) with per\u2011night rates.  \n* **Itemised budget calculator** (accommodation, food, transport, entry fees, misc).  \n* **Practical travel tips** (how to move around, what to pack, safety, best time to visit).\n\n---\n\n## 1\ufe0f\u20e3 DAY\u2011BY\u2011DAY ITINERARY  \n\n> **Assumptions** \u2013 You\u2019ll arrive in Goa by flight or train the night before Day\u202f1 (or early on Day\u202f1). The plan starts from **Panaji (the capital)**, which is a convenient base for both North and South Goa. All times are approximate and can be shifted by a few minutes depending on traffic and personal pace.\n\n| Day | Time | Activity | Details & Travel Time |\n|-----|------|----------|-----------------------|\n| **Day\u202f1 \u2013 North Goa Highlights** | **08:00\u202f\u2013\u202f09:00** | **Breakfast** at the hotel or a local caf\u00e9 (e.g., *Cafe Bodega*). | Typical Indian breakfast: idli\u2011vada, poha, fresh juice \u2013 \u20b9150\u2011\u20b9250. |\n| | **09:00\u202f\u2013\u202f10:30** | **Fort Aguada & Lighthouse** | 5\u202fkm from Panaji (\u2248\u202f15\u202fmin by scooter). Entry free; small fee for lighthouse (\u20b920). |\n| | **10:30\u202f\u2013\u202f12:00** | **Sinquerim Beach** \u2013 quick dip or sunrise walk. | 2\u202fkm from Fort Aguada (\u2248\u202f5\u202fmin). |\n| | **12:00\u202f\u2013\u202f13:30** | **Lunch** at *Martin\u2019s Corner* (Baga) \u2013 Goan seafood thali. | \u20b9350\u2011\u20b9500. |\n| | **13:30\u202f\u2013\u202f15:30** | **Calangute & Baga Beaches** \u2013 water\u2011sports (optional jet\u2011ski, parasailing). | Activity cost: \u20b9800\u2011\u20b91,200 per person (choose one). |\n| | **15:30\u202f\u2013\u202f16:30** | **Anjuna Flea Market** (Wednesday\u2011Saturday) \u2013 shop for souvenirs, jewellery, handicrafts. | No entry fee; budget \u20b9500\u2011\u20b91,000 for shopping. |\n| | **16:30\u202f\u2013\u202f18:00** | **Chapora Fort** \u2013 sunset view over Vagator Beach. | 6\u202fkm from Anjuna (\u2248\u202f15\u202fmin). Entry free. |\n| | **18:00\u202f\u2013\u202f20:00** | **Dinner** at *Thalassa* (Vagator) \u2013 Greek\u2011Goan fusion, great sunset vibe. | \u20b9600\u2011\u20b9900 per person. |\n| | **20:00\u202f\u2013\u202f22:00** | **Nightlife** \u2013 optional bar/club (e.g., *Club Cabana*). | Drinks \u20b9300\u2011\u20b9600. Return to hotel by 22:30. |\n| **Day\u202f2 \u2013 South Goa Relaxation** | **08:00\u202f\u2013\u202f09:00** | **Breakfast** at hotel or *Brittany Caf\u00e9* (Colva). | \u20b9150\u2011\u20b9250. |\n| | **09:00\u202f\u2013\u202f10:30** | **Drive to Colva Beach** (\u2248\u202f45\u202fkm, 1\u202fh 15\u202fmin). | Scenic coastal road; stop for photos. |\n| | **10:30\u202f\u2013\u202f12:30** | **Colva & Benaulim Beaches** \u2013 sunbathing, optional dolphin\u2011watching boat (\u20b91,200 per person). |\n| | **12:30\u202f\u2013\u202f13:30** | **Lunch** at *Martin\u2019s Corner* (Colva) \u2013 Goan chicken xacuti. | \u20b9350\u2011\u20b9500. |\n| | **13:30\u202f\u2013\u202f15:00** | **Cabo de Rama Fort** \u2013 historic ruins & panoramic sea view. | 20\u202fkm from Colva (\u2248\u202f30\u202fmin). Entry free. |\n| | **15:00\u202f\u2013\u202f16:30** | **Palolem Beach** \u2013 calm waters, hammocks, coconut water. | 30\u202fkm from Cabo (\u2248\u202f45\u202fmin). |\n| | **16:30\u202f\u2013\u202f18:00** | **Kayaking in the backwaters** (optional) \u2013 \u20b9800 per person. |\n| | **18:00\u202f\u2013\u202f19:30** | **Sunset at Agonda Beach** \u2013 quieter spot, perfect for photos. |\n| | **19:30\u202f\u2013\u202f21:00** | **Dinner** at *Martin\u2019s Corner* (Agonda) or *Ritz Caf\u00e9* \u2013 Goan fish curry & rice. | \u20b9350\u2011\u20b9600. |\n| | **21:00\u202f\u2013\u202f22:30** | **Return to Panaji** (\u2248\u202f1\u202fh 15\u202fmin) \u2013 pack, relax. | If you have a late flight/train, stay near the airport; otherwise, enjoy a nightcap at a local bar. |\n\n### Quick \u201cWhat\u2011to\u2011Pack\u201d Checklist\n- Light cotton clothing, swimwear, flip\u2011flops + comfortable shoes for forts.\n- Sunscreen (SPF\u202f30+), sunglasses, hat.\n- Small day\u2011backpack, reusable water bottle.\n- Power bank, universal plug adapter (India uses Type\u202fC/D/M, 230\u202fV).\n- Cash (\u20b9) for small vendors; most places accept cards, but keep \u20b92,000\u2011\u20b93,000 handy for markets.\n\n---\n\n## 2\ufe0f\u20e3 HOTEL RECOMMENDATIONS  \n\n| Category | Hotel (Location) | Approx. Rate (per night, INR) | Key Amenities | Why It Fits the Itinerary |\n|----------|------------------|------------------------------|----------------|---------------------------|\n| **Budget** | **Casa De Goa \u2013 Heritage Home** (Panaji) | **\u20b92,500 \u2013 3,200** (double occupancy) | Free Wi\u2011Fi, rooftop garden, air\u2011conditioned rooms, breakfast included. | Central location \u2192 easy to reach North & South Goa; walking distance to Miramar Beach. |\n| **Mid\u2011Range** | **The Flora Residency** (Candolim, North Goa) | **\u20b95,500 \u2013 7,000** | Outdoor pool, sea\u2011view rooms, on\u2011site restaurant, 24\u202fh front desk. | Near Calangute/Baga \u2192 saves travel time on Day\u202f1; still a short drive to South Goa on Day\u202f2. |\n| **Luxury** | **Taj Exotica Resort & Spa** (Benaulim, South Goa) | **\u20b918,000 \u2013 22,000** | Private beach, spa, multiple dining venues, infinity pool, concierge. | Perfect if you want a pampered night after Day\u202f1 and a relaxed Day\u202f2 on the South\u2011Goa coast. |\n\n> **Tip:** All three hotels can be booked via major portals (Booking.com, MakeMyTrip) with free cancellation up to 24\u202fh before check\u2011in. Prices shown are for **standard double rooms** in the high\u2011season (Oct\u2011Mar). Off\u2011season rates can be 30\u201140\u202f% lower.\n\n---\n\n## 3\ufe0f\u20e3 BUDGET CALCULATOR (INR)\n\n| Item | Cost (\u20b9) | Details |\n|------|----------|---------|\n| **Accommodation (2 nights)** | **Budget**: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b92,800 = **\u20b95,600**<br>**Mid\u2011Range**: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b96,200 = **\u20b912,400**<br>**Luxury**: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b920,000 = **\u20b940,000** | Rates are average per night (incl. taxes). |\n| **Food & Drinks** (2\u202fdays) | Breakfast: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b9200 = \u20b9400<br>Lunch: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b9450 = \u20b9900<br>Dinner: 2\u202f\u00d7\u202f\u20b9750 = \u20b91,500<br>Snacks/Drinks: \u20b9600 | **Total** \u2248 **\u20b93,400** per person (mid\u2011range). |\n| **Local Transport** | Scooter rental (\u20b9350\u202f/\u202fday) \u00d7\u202f2 = \u20b9700<br>Fuel (\u2248\u202f30\u202fkm\u202f/\u202fday, \u20b990\u202f/\u202fL, 30\u202fL total) = \u20b92,700<br>Occasional auto\u2011rickshaw/taxi for night out = \u20b9500 | **Total** \u2248 **\u20b93,900** |\n| **Attraction Fees & Activities** | Fort Aguada lighthouse \u20b920<br>Water\u2011sports (choose one) \u20b91,000<br>Dolphin\u2011watch boat (optional) \u20b91,200<br>Kayaking (optional) \u20b9800<br>Misc (market souvenirs) \u20b91,000 | **Total (with optional activities)** \u2248 **\u20b94,020** |\n| **Miscellaneous** (tips, laundry, emergency cash) | \u20b91,000 |\n| **Grand Total (per person)** | **Budget\u2011Hotel combo**: \u20b95,600 + \u20b93,400 + \u20b93,900 + \u20b94,020 + \u20b91,000 \u2248 **\u20b917,920**<br>**Mid\u2011Range combo**: \u20b912,400 + \u20b93,400 + \u20b93,900 + \u20b94,020 + \u20b91,000 \u2248 **\u20b924,720**<br>**Luxury combo**: \u20b940,000 + \u20b93,400 + \u20b93,900 + \u20b94,020 + \u20b91,000 \u2248 **\u20b952,320** |\n| **Your Target** | **\u20b950,000** | The **mid\u2011range** option comfortably fits under \u20b950k. If you prefer a splurge, you can stay at the luxury resort for one night and a budget hotel the other night to stay within the limit. |\n\n### Sample \u201cMid\u2011Range\u201d Cost Breakdown (most realistic for \u20b950k)\n\n| Category | Amount (\u20b9) |\n|----------|------------|\n| Hotel (2 nights, The Flora Residency) | 12,400 |\n| Food & Drinks | 3,400 |\n| Transport (scooter + fuel + occasional taxi) | 3,900 |\n| Activities & Entry Fees | 4,020 |\n| Miscellaneous | 1,000 |\n| **Total** | **\u20b924,720** (\u2248\u202f\u20b912,360 per day) |\n\n*If you are traveling with a companion and sharing a room, the accommodation cost halves, bringing the per\u2011person total to **\u2248\u202f\u20b913,000** \u2013 well under your \u20b950k budget, leaving plenty for extra shopping or a spa treatment.*\n\n---\n\n## 4\ufe0f\u20e3 PRACTICAL TRAVEL TIPS & RECOMMENDATIONS  \n\n| Topic | Advice |\n|-------|--------|\n| **Best Time to Visit** | **Oct\u202f\u2013\u202fMar** (cool, dry, peak tourist season). Avoid monsoon (Jun\u2011Sep) unless you love rain\u2011soaked scenery. |\n| **Getting to Goa** | Fly into **Dabolim Airport (GOI)** \u2013 cheap flights from major Indian metros. From the airport, take a prepaid taxi (\u2248\u202f\u20b9800) to your hotel or pick up your pre\u2011booked scooter at the airport kiosk. |\n| **Getting Around** | **Rent a scooter** (\u20b9300\u2011\u20b9400\u202f/\u202fday). It\u2019s the most flexible, cheap, and popular way to explore both coasts. Carry a valid driving licence (Indian or International). For longer distances (e.g., Panaji \u2192 South Goa), a **private cab** (\u20b92,500\u2011\u20b93,000) is comfortable. |\n| **Safety** | Goa is tourist\u2011friendly. Keep an eye on your belongings on crowded beaches and markets. Avoid isolated beaches after dark unless you\u2019re with a group. Drink bottled water. |\n| **Currency** | ATMs are plentiful in Panaji, Calangute, and South Goa. Keep some cash for small stalls; most restaurants accept cards. |\n| **Connectivity** | 4G coverage is excellent. Buy a local SIM (Jio, Airtel) at the airport for ~\u20b9200 with 2\u202fGB data. |\n| **Cultural Etiquette** | Dress modestly when visiting churches or temples (cover shoulders/knees). Remove shoes before entering places of worship. Tipping 5\u201110\u202f% in restaurants is appreciated. |\n| **Must\u2011Try Foods** | *Goan fish curry*, *prawn balch\u00e3o*, *bebinca* (dessert), *feni* (local cashew spirit) \u2013 try in reputable eateries. |\n| **Eco\u2011Friendly Tips** | Use refillable water bottles, avoid single\u2011use plastics, and respect beach clean\u2011up signs. |\n\n---\n\n## 5\ufe0f\u20e3 QUICK \u201cTO\u2011DO\u201d CHECKLIST (Before You Leave)\n\n1. **Book flights** (arrive night before Day\u202f1 or early morning).  \n2. **Reserve hotel** (choose budget/mid\u2011range/luxury).  \n3. **Pre\u2011book scooter** (many hotels arrange it; otherwise, rent at the airport).  \n4. **Download offline maps** (Google Maps offline for Panaji\u2011Baga\u2011Colva corridor).  \n5. **Pack** (light clothing, sunscreen, hat, reusable bottle, basic meds).  \n6. **Arrange travel insurance** (covers medical emergencies, lost luggage).  \n7. **Notify bank** of travel dates (to avoid card blocks).  \n\n---\n\n### \ud83c\udf89 Ready to Go!\n\n- **If you want a comfortable, hassle\u2011free trip** \u2013 go with the **mid\u2011range hotel** (The Flora Residency) and follow the itinerary above.  \n- **If you\u2019re traveling solo or with a friend** \u2013 share a budget hotel and you\u2019ll stay well under \u20b920k total, leaving plenty for extra activities or souvenirs.  \n- **If you crave a splurge** \u2013 spend one night at **Taj Exotica** (South Goa) and the other night at a budget stay; you\u2019ll still land close to the \u20b950k ceiling.\n\nEnjoy the sun, sea, and spice\u2011laden flavors of Goa! \ud83c\udf1e\ud83c\udfd6\ufe0f\ud83d\udea4 Feel free to ask for any tweaks (e.g., vegetarian food options, alternative beaches, or a different travel date) and I\u2019ll fine\u2011tune the plan for you. Happy travels!"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "fc_10aafffc-cd71-4aee-8c35-856eaa4e8b55", "function": {"arguments": "{\"destination\":\"Fort Aguada, Goa, India\",\"source\":\"Panaji, Goa, India\"}", "name": "google_map_tool"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Error occured in python script name [C:\\AI_2026\\Projects\\1_TravelBot\\HolidayAgent\\Tools\\GoogleMap.py] line number [13] error message [HolidayAgentException.__init__() missing 1 required positional argument: 'error_detail']", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "fc_10aafffc-cd71-4aee-8c35-856eaa4e8b55"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Travel_Planner", "content": "## \ud83d\udd27 What the error means\n\n```\nHolidayAgentException.__init__() missing 1 required positional argument: 'error_detail'\n```\n\nThe traceback tells us that somewhere in **`GoogleMap.py`** (line\u202f13) you are raising (or creating) an instance of `HolidayAgentException`, but the constructor (`__init__`) of that exception class expects **two** arguments:\n\n```python\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, error_message, error_detail):\n        super().__init__(error_message)\n        self.detail = error_detail\n```\n\nIf you call it like:\n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Something went wrong\")\n```\n\nyou only pass the first argument (`error_message`). Python then complains that the required second argument (`error_detail`) is missing.\n\n---\n\n## \u2705 Quick fixes you can apply\n\n### 1\ufe0f\u20e3 Provide the missing argument when raising the exception  \n\nAdd a second argument (it can be an empty string, `None`, or a more detailed message).\n\n```python\n# Before (causing the error)\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Google Maps API call failed\")\n\n# After \u2013 supply a detail string (or None)\nraise HolidayAgentException(\n    \"Google Maps API call failed\",\n    \"Timeout after 10 seconds while requesting directions\"\n)\n```\n\nIf you don\u2019t have a specific detail, you can simply pass `\"\"` or `None`:\n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Google Maps API call failed\", \"\")\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2\ufe0f\u20e3 Give the constructor a default value for `error_detail`\n\nIf you want the exception to be usable with a single argument throughout the codebase, modify the class definition to make `error_detail` optional:\n\n```python\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, error_message, error_detail=None):\n        super().__init__(error_message)\n        self.detail = error_detail\n```\n\nNow both of these are valid:\n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Google Maps API call failed\")\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Google Maps API call failed\", \"Timeout\")\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3\ufe0f\u20e3 Use a helper function to wrap the raise (optional but tidy)\n\nIf you raise this exception in many places, a small helper can keep the code clean:\n\n```python\ndef raise_holiday_error(msg, detail=None):\n    raise HolidayAgentException(msg, detail)\n\n#