entException` (or any call to that class). | That line is currently passing only one argument. |\n| **3\ufe0f\u20e3 Add the missing argument** | Either supply a detail string (`"some detail"`), `None`, or `""`. | Satisfies the constructor signature. |\n| **4\ufe0f\u20e3 (Optional) Make the class flexible** | Edit the exception class to give `error_detail` a default value (`None`). | Prevents the same mistake elsewhere. |\n| **5\ufe0f\u20e3 Run a quick test** | Execute the function that calls Google Maps (use a valid API key). | Confirms the error is gone and the function works. |\n| **6\ufe0f\u20e3 Add logging (recommended)** | Before raising, log the error: `logging.error("Google Maps failed: %s", response.text)`. | Gives you a record if the API fails again. |\n\n---\n\n## \U0001f4e6 Example of a **fully corrected** `GoogleMap.py` (minimal version)\n\n```python\n# --------------------------------------------------------------\n# C:\\AI_2026\\Projects\\1_TravelBot\\HolidayAgent\\Tools\\GoogleMap.py\n# --------------------------------------------------------------\nimport logging\nimport requests\nfrom ..exceptions import HolidayAgentException   # adjust import as needed\n\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------\ndef get_route(origin: str, destination: str, api_key: str) -> dict:\n    """\n    Calls Google Directions API and returns the parsed JSON.\n    Raises HolidayAgentException with a helpful detail string on failure.\n    """\n    url = (\n        "https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/directions/json"\n        f"?origin={origin}&destination={destination}&key={api_key}"\n    )\n    try:\n        response = requests.get(url, timeout=10)\n    except requests.RequestException as exc:\n        # Network\u2011level problem (DNS, timeout, etc.)\n        raise HolidayAgentException(\n            "Unable to reach Google Maps API",\n            str(exc)\n        ) from exc\n\n    # ---- HTTP status check --------------------------------------